President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the State of New Mexico, providing federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts following severe storms and flooding from July 25 to August 9, 2010. The declaration allows for federal funding on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures in Cibola, McKinley, Mora, San Juan, and Socorro Counties. Sandy Coachman has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.